This article is a transcript of a press briefing by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs. The briefing covers a range of topics including the extension of the First-Time Homebuyer Tax Credit, the unemployment insurance provision, the BP oil spill, the lifting of the ban on U.S. military assistance to Indonesia's special forces unit, the lawsuit against Arizona's immigration law, and the controversy surrounding Shirley Sherrod. Gibbs discusses the President's apology to Sherrod and emphasizes the need for reflection and learning from this situation. He also addresses questions about the President's views on race and discrimination, the extension of the Bush tax cuts, and the small business tax cuts. Overall, the briefing provides information on various issues and events happening at the time.